}
  HEXEDIT file [position]

This command lets you edit the
contents of a file. If you give a
starting position, editing begins at
that point. The start position
must be specified as hexadecimal
number.

It shows the file position, the old
hex value, and allows you to enter a
new hex value, or press <RETURN> to
leave the value unchanged.

Press <ESC> to exit the command.
